  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON : The proposed extension to the rear roof slope of the dwellinghouse and the existing 2 storey projection is considered by reason of its design, siting and materials to cause significant harm to the symmetry of the terrace, the historic architectural integrity of the property and the character and appearance of the conservation area being visible to views from Beversbrook Road.  The proposal is not considered to comply with the objectives of policies D1 (Overall Design), D4 (Designing in Context), D11 (Extensions and Alterations), D24 (Materials), D25 (Roof Extensions) and D28 (Roof Extensions) of the Islington Unitary Development Plan, parts 2.4 and 2.5 of the Islington Urban Design Guide and paragraphs 24.10, 24.12, 24.13, 24.20 and 24.21 of the Mercers Road/Tavistock Terrace Conservation Area Design Guidelines"
